00:14:24.833 --> 00:14:25.633
Have some ghost-to-Living
etiquette.

411
00:14:27.167 --> 00:14:29.103
MELANIE:
After he sold
the car dealership.

412
00:14:29.203 --> 00:14:30.538
then he ran for mayor.

413
00:14:30.638 --> 00:14:32.607
I saw even less of him then.

414
00:14:32.707 --> 00:14:34.074
So you took him down. but then.

415
00:14:34.174 --> 00:14:35.744
instead of spending
more time with you.

416
00:14:35.844 --> 00:14:37.878
he just dove into a new project.

417
00:14:37.978 --> 00:14:39.279
Exactly.

418
00:14:39.380 --> 00:14:41.048
He's never
going to stop working.

419
00:14:41.148 --> 00:14:42.316
She's a bit of a bummer. but

420
00:14:42.416 --> 00:14:44.151
you've got to feel
for the broad.

421
00:14:44.251 --> 00:14:45.587
(sighs)

422
00:14:45.687 --> 00:14:48.889
-(chuckles) Melanie.
-MELANIE: Tad?

423
00:14:48.989 --> 00:14:50.725
What are you doing here?

424
00:14:50.825 --> 00:14:52.126
I'm picking up my moo shu pork.

425
00:14:52.226 --> 00:14:54.796
Jay recommended
this place to me.

426
00:14:54.895 --> 00:14:56.497
Jay. you recommended
this place to Tad

427
00:14:56.598 --> 00:14:58.966
and suggested it to Melanie
for our secret meeting?

428
00:14:59.066 --> 00:15:01.135
Well. it's a great place.
but they're not doing very well.

429
00:15:01.235 --> 00:15:02.970
I'm just trying to support them.

430
00:15:03.170 --> 00:15:05.507
-What's she talking about.
secret meeting?
-(Melanie sighs)

431
00:15:05.607 --> 00:15:07.040
I'm tired of this.

432
00:15:08.208 --> 00:15:10.144
Tad.

433
