483
00:17:22.510 --> 00:17:25.078
We are watching
a once-in-a-generation talent.

484
00:17:25.178 --> 00:17:27.815
And the clasp is an onion ring.

485
00:17:27.916 --> 00:17:30.552
-What a mind.
-SAMANTHA: Uh. Tad.

486
00:17:30.652 --> 00:17:32.252
there's someone here to see you.

487
00:17:32.352 --> 00:17:35.122
I came to apologize.

488
00:17:35.222 --> 00:17:37.124
It's true. I've been unhappy.

489
00:17:37.224 --> 00:17:40.260
but I never should have
blown the whistle on Gate-gate.

490
00:17:40.360 --> 00:17:42.296
In my defense. I had just

491
00:17:42.396 --> 00:17:45.232
polished off a box of white zin.
(laughs)

492
00:17:45.332 --> 00:17:46.801
She'd probably get along
really well

493
00:17:46.901 --> 00:17:48.503
with that wino Lucille Ball.

494
00:17:48.603 --> 00:17:49.938
-(chuckles)
-TAD: Honestly.

495
00:17:50.038 --> 00:17:52.472
I'm not mad at you.
You were desperate.

496
00:17:52.574 --> 00:17:55.510
And it's true.
I-I-I do love my work.

497
00:17:56.711 --> 00:17:58.012
But I also love you.

498
00:17:58.111 --> 00:18:01.248
so I'm not sure
where that leaves us.

499
00:18:01.348 --> 00:18:03.017
Well. here's a "cake
and eat it. too" suggestion.

500
00:18:03.116 --> 00:18:05.485
He wants to work. she wants
to spend more time together.

501
00:18:05.587 --> 00:18:07.522
What if they took a page
out of the Sam and Jay playbook

502
00:18:07.622 --> 00:18:09.189
and worked together?

503
00:18:09.389 --> 00:18:11.358
What if there was a way
that you could still be mayor

504
00:18:11.458 --> 00:18:13.861
and also spend
more time together?

505
00:18:13.962 --> 00:18:15.630
By being like me and Jay?

506
00:18:15.730 --> 00:18:17.364
-What do you mean?
-Cash-strapped?

507
00:18:17.464 --> 00:18:19.299
-Inept at business?
-Friendless?

508
00:18:19.399 --> 00:18:21.168
Maybe you could work together
at the mayor's office.

509
00:18:21.268 --> 00:18:23.705
Oh. I would love
to work with Tad. but...

510
00:18:23.805 --> 00:18:26.473
I don't know if I'm built
for the world of politics.

511
00:18:26.574 --> 00:18:29.043
I don't know. that was pretty
manipulative and underhanded.

512
00:18:29.142 --> 00:18:30.812
the way you derailed
Tad's career.

513
00:18:30.912 --> 00:18:32.346
That's true.

514
00:18:32.446 --> 00:18:33.881
She could be
your chief of staff.

515
00:18:33.982 --> 00:18:35.516
Oh. uh. I already have one.

516
00:18:35.617 --> 00:18:37.117
Not after you throw Jeremy
under the bus

517
00:18:37.217 --> 00:18:38.953
for any residual
Gate-gate fallout.

518
00:18:39.053 --> 00:18:40.822
My God. that came to her easily.

519
00:18:40.922 --> 00:18:44.191
I like it. We're gonna do
great things together.

520
00:18:44.291 --> 00:18:46.226
We could even do some traveling.

521
00:18:46.326 --> 00:18:49.329
like you wanted.
but on the city's dime.

522
00:18:49.429 --> 00:18:51.198
He heard he's getting
his job back five seconds ago.

523
00:18:51.298 --> 00:18:52.867
and he's already knee-deep
in new corruption.

524
00:18:52.967 --> 00:18:54.134
JAY:
Oh. no.

525
00:18:54.502 --> 00:18:56.037
You probably won't have time
to be the mayor

526
00:18:56.136 --> 00:18:58.973
and run a world-class
breastaurant. though. huh?

527
00:18:59.073 --> 00:19:02.376
That's true. but I don't want it
happening without me. (sighs)

528
00:19:02.476 --> 00:19:04.979
I'm gonna have to pull the plug
on Mountains of the Valley.

529
00:19:05.079 --> 00:19:07.347
You can still put
jalapeño knockers

530
00:19:07.447 --> 00:19:09.249
on the Mahesh menu if you want.

531
00:19:09.349 --> 00:19:12.219
Thank you. I will take that
under serious consideration.

532
00:19:12.319 --> 00:19:14.354
Thank you guys for everything.

533
00:19:14.454 --> 00:19:16.223
TAD:
We got to go.

534
00:19:16.323 --> 00:19:17.592
but we'll write you
from St. Kitts.

535
00:19:17.692 --> 00:19:19.761
where we'll be on a catamaran.

536
00:19:19.861 --> 00:19:22.664
working tirelessly
for the people of Ulster County.

537
00:19:23.765 --> 00:19:25.399
And in the end
it all worked out.

538
00:19:25.499 --> 00:19:27.535
The girl got the guy.
the guy got the job.

539
00:19:27.635 --> 00:19:31.072
and I got to smell something
called moo shu three ways.

540
00:19:31.171 --> 00:19:33.407
Which. ironically.
was the name of the move

541
00:19:33.508 --> 00:19:36.110
Gus was doing on that tape.

542
00:19:41.314 --> 00:19:42.884
<i>NEWSCASTER (over TV):</i>
<i>Well. it seems that Mayor Tad</i>

543
00:19:42.984 --> 00:19:44.519
<i>has somehow survived</i>
<i>the Gate-gate scandal</i>

544
00:19:44.619 --> 00:19:46.286
<i>and will not be</i>
<i>stepping down anytime soon.</i>

545
00:19:46.386 --> 00:19:49.090
Oh. good news for Tad.
bad news for jalapeño knockers.

546
00:19:49.189 --> 00:19:50.490
Yeah. sorry. Trevor.

547
00:19:50.892 --> 00:19:53.061
This is a setback for the
upscale breastaurant industry

548
00:19:53.161 --> 00:19:54.729
as a whole.

549
00:19:54.829 --> 00:19:56.931
But we have been through worse
and we will be back.

550
00:19:57.031 --> 00:19:58.633
<i>And in a surprising twist.</i>

551
00:19:58.733 --> 00:20:00.367
<i>Tad's return to office was</i>
<i>aided</i>

552
00:20:00.467 --> 00:20:04.371
<i>by a longtime political foe--</i>
<i>Gus Heyward.</i>

553
00:20:04.471 --> 00:20:06.941
<i>I caught up with the</i>
<i>city councilman earlier today.</i>

554
00:20:07.041 --> 00:20:08.876
<i>That's the thing about</i>
<i>politics.</i>

555
00:20:08.976 --> 00:20:11.713
<i>You never know when people</i>
<i>are going to come together.</i>

556
00:20:11.813 --> 00:20:13.581
That language felt purposeful.

557
00:20:13.681 --> 00:20:15.550
-I think you're probably
reading into it.
<i>-My point is.</i>

558
00:20:15.650 --> 00:20:17.284
<i>you have to be flexible.</i>

559
00:20:17.384 --> 00:20:19.821
<i>Sometimes you just have</i>
<i>to reach across the aisle</i>

560
00:20:19.921 --> 00:20:21.622
<i>and give someone a hand.</i>

561
00:20:21.723 --> 00:20:23.758
Okay. well.
there's no reading into that.

562
00:20:23.858 --> 00:20:25.193
Okay. yeah. this guy's a freak.

563
00:20:25.593 --> 00:20:27.729
He did that same wink
on the tape. Ugh. it haunts me.

564
00:20:27.829 --> 00:20:29.163
<i>NEWSCASTER:</i>
<i>And now let's turn it over</i>

565
00:20:29.564 --> 00:20:32.934
<i>to brand-new Channel Five</i>
<i>weatherwoman Nikki Snow.</i>

566
00:20:33.034 --> 00:20:36.738
<i>A cold front is expected to</i>
<i>move in over the next few days.</i>

567
00:20:36.838 --> 00:20:39.239
Wait. is that the bartender
from Mountains of the Valley?

568
00:20:39.339 --> 00:20:42.577
-Yes.
-Glad she landed on her feet.

569
00:20:42.677 --> 00:20:44.712
Can't keep
that kind of talent down.
